Non-functional — answers:
Volume:

Ad impression events: 2M events/sec peak (AVOD tier, 50M subscribers)
Two sources × 2M = up to 4M events/sec total ingestion
Each event: ~1 KB (richer payload than viewership events)
Peak ingestion throughput: ~4 GB/sec

Latency SLA:
LayerSLAAd Ops live dashboard< 5 minutesAdvertiser hourly report< 1 hourFinance billing reconciliationT+1 (next day, exact counts)ML online features< 50ms serving
Data retention:

Raw impression events: 7 years (financial records — advertiser billing disputes can come years later)
Aggregated campaign metrics: 7 years
Audit log of reconciliation runs: 7 years immutable
Note: this is significantly longer than viewership (90 days) — financial data has different retention rules

PII:

user_id is PII — mask at stream processing layer
Advertiser reports must never contain user-level PII — only aggregated counts
ML features: pseudonymised user_id (tokenized, not raw)

Spikes:

Predictable spikes: primetime (8–11pm), live sports, award shows
Spike multiplier: 5x on baseline (less extreme than viewership because AVOD is a subset of total subscribers)
Ad auctions also spike during high-value content — NBA finals, Oscars


